Body: Description: A report called BT_Billing does not getting generated with its attributes. An error while executing the analysis for an attribute called 'Company'.
Invitation updated. Attendees: No attendees listed
Invitation updated. Attendees: Saqib Sharif, Brige PG

What We've Learned Updated: Customer has a custom SQL Analysis that has two tasks. One is to get data from multiple tables and views and essentially create another DB table in SQL. The second task exports that data using reports functionality and drops it at a location as a CSV file.

There were two SQL views that had a column name ""Company" due to which SQL task 1 was not running.

During our meeting today, we corrected the reference to "company" column in the SELECT statement. Job is now running
Next Steps Updated: I will follow up tomorrow with the customer as the job takes 20-25 minutes to complete.

Steps to Reproduce Updated: In SQL DB, reference two or more tables/views with same column name present in all of them in a SQL script and you will get an error:
Ambiguous Column Name: COLUMN_NAME
